featured_reviews.review_id: A little known historical place in Hooghly adjacent to Bandel Church where a Garh (settlement) used to be during the period of Hussein Shah. The township's name is a Portuguese derivative from Ugolim and Bon del. Bonomasjid had been rediscovered in the early twentieth century from a forest zone (Bon), generating the name. Used to be a placid, semi village till the 1980s. Now it is  a sprawling mohalla of Hooghly Chinsurah Municipality that somehow retained its molecular past here and there in an unkempt fashion.
